# Operational Reporting Model

## Overview

Operational reporting consolidates data from order management systems, logistics platforms, and financial systems to provide visibility into wholesale performance.

These reports allow operations teams and leadership to track key operational activities and identify potential issues before they impact service levels.

---

## Purpose

Operational reporting helps organizations:

• monitor order status and fulfillment progress  
• track shipment performance  
• evaluate financial accuracy  
• measure operational KPIs  
• support strategic decision making

Effective reporting enables organizations to manage operations proactively.

---

## Common Operational Reports

Wholesale operations teams commonly generate reports such as:

• order status reports  
• shipment performance reports  
• inventory availability reports  
• chargeback analysis reports  
• operational KPI dashboards  

These reports provide insight into different areas of operational performance.

---

## Reporting Data Sources

Operational reports often draw data from multiple systems, including:

• ERP systems  
• warehouse management systems  
• EDI platforms  
• financial systems  
• inventory management tools  

Combining these data sources provides a comprehensive view of operations.

---

## Reporting Formats

Operational reports may be delivered in several formats:

• spreadsheet reports  
• dashboard visualizations  
• automated ERP reports  
• business intelligence tools

These formats allow teams to analyze operational data efficiently.

---

## Operational Impact

Well-designed reporting models allow operations teams to:

• identify process bottlenecks  
• track performance trends  
• improve decision making  
• support cross-functional coordination

These insights strengthen operational performance across the organization.

---

## Final Note

Operational reporting provides the visibility needed to manage wholesale operations effectively. When data is organized and accessible, organizations can respond quickly to operational risks and performance issues.
